<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="467" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d467">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">865.857 An 2/96½</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <gloss type="from">Wilson</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hot Springs, Va.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-26">
                                    <hi rend="italic">26 December, 1915</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: This is encouraging as
                            to the spirit of the Austro-Hungarian government, but I fear they are
                            preparing to contest the facts with us, and the inferences to be drawn
                            from them.</p>
                        <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>